text: It's been years I have been feelings this way & I know people deal with so much worse so it makes me feel guilting that I'm even complaining
In a way I am but I just really feel alone and I'm losing my grip on what everything is happening.
I feel the need to vent to someone but I already vent too much that I don't want to come off as attention seeking
I don't even have control over my body. I feel so weak and can barely manage to walk.
It's as if depression makes a huge deal out of everything like nothing bad is happening but yet I'm having so many thoughts
I'm trying not worry people and next thing you know I pass out during dance practice due to malnutrition.
But I wonder, how would I treat myself if I was in a different body looking at who I am now?
I hate that I can't eat without breaking down afterwards.
Some of my posts could be triggering to some, I am not pro- anything. Simply ranting. So please unfollow if you're not okay with that.
When it comes to other people, I don't judge them a bit but when it comes to me; oh that's a whole different story.
So many people dying and I'm here wasting my youth.
I'm filled with a void of emptiness and it's exhausting attempting to find things to fill myself up in.

"Some people are so poor all they have is money."

Well I want to be "poor" now.

The child has grown
The dream is gone
And I have become
Comfortably numb.

I'm getting worse. 

But I don't know how to stop myself from falling any deeper.
